<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/563000071/2025-26/evaluation> a ns1:EvaluationSystem ;
    ns1:evaluationDescription """1. ORDINARY CALL
Through Progressive Assessment
Three contributions to the grade:
a. Individual Project. It weighs 20% of the final grade. Topic, formats, date of delivery and rules will be established by the coordinator at the beginning of the course.
b. Team Project. It weighs 30% of the final grade. Team composition, topic, formats, date of delivery or presentation, and other details will be established by the coordinator at the beginning of the course.
c. Global test. It weighs 50% of the final grade. It is an individual written exam with theory, problems, applications, cases, etc. on the overall content of the course. The minimum score in the global test (c) will be 4/10 in order to average the scores of the 3 contributions (a,,b,,c), otherwise it will not be averaged the global test together with the projects scores, and the final grade in the ordinary call will be that of the global test.

2. EXTRAORDINARY CALL
In the extraordinary call of exams, the assessment will be through a written final exam that weighs 80% and the grade of the Individual Project 20%. The minimum score in the exam must be 4/10 in order to average the score with the Induvidual Project score. Otherwise the final grade in the extraordinary call will be that of the exam.
To pass 5/10 points or over are necessary in the weighted average to pass."""@es ;
    ns1:hasEvaluationTrial <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/563000071/2025-26/evaluation/trial1>,
